bayStackEapExtMib.name: bayStackEapExtMib

revisions.description: v027: Added the padding bit in bseeMultihostNonEapRadiusPasswordAttributeFormat
v026: Added support for NEAP freeform password
v018: Added bseeMultiHostStatusVid, bseeMultiHostStatusPri, bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusVid, bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusPri.
v016: Added support for fail-open and voip vlan.
v015: Added support for using most recent RADIUS-assigned vlan.
v014: Added support for EAPOL supplicants.

v010 Added support for various additional EAP features: - allowing IP phones based on DHCP - allowing use of radius assigned VLAN in multihost-eap mode - use of unicast packets for Eap-ReqId packets - fail or not-fail EAP users on radius timeout (default is to fail)
v009: Added non-eap ubp support, filter-on-mac ubp support, configurable non-eap radius password attribute format support, re-auth of individual MAC addrs support.
v008: Added MHSA support. Added new non-eap auth reasons.
v007: Cleaned up some DESCRIPTION clauses. Added bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusTable.
v006: Added objects: bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapClient bseeMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapClient bseePortConfigMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapClient deprecated bseePortConfigMultiHostNonEapMacSource.
v004: Changes to have separate enable/disable flag for guest vlan and remediation vlan. Added objects: bseeGuestVlanEnabled bseeRemediationVlanEnabled bseePortConfigGuestVlanEnabled
v003: Added enhancements for guest vlan, remediation vlan, and multihost support.

bseeUserBasedPoliciesEnabled.name: bseeUserBasedPoliciesEnabled
bseeUserBasedPoliciesEnabled.description: This object indicates whether EAPOL User-based policies are enabled or disabled.

bseeGuestVlanId.name: bseeGuestVlanId
bseeGuestVlanId.description: This object specifies the ID of the global default guest VLAN. This VLAN is used for ports which do not have a configured guest VLAN. Access to the guest VLAN is allowed for MAC addresses before EAP authentication has been performed. However, if the value of bseeGuestVlanEnabled is false(2), then access to the guest VLAN is not allowed for ports that do not have a configured guest VLAN.

bseeRemediationVlanId.name: bseeRemediationVlanId
bseeRemediationVlanId.description: This object specifies the ID of the remediation VLAN. If EAP authentication fails for a port, MAC addresses on that port are restricted to access only the remediation VLAN. However, if the value of bseeRemediationVlanEnabled is false(2), then access is not allowed at all for a port when EAP authentication fails.

bseeMaximumEapClientMacs.name: bseeMaximumEapClientMacs
bseeMaximumEapClientMacs.description: This object specifies the global maximum number of EAP authenticated MAC addresses allowed.

bseeMaximumNonEapClientMacs.name: bseeMaximumNonEapClientMacs
bseeMaximumNonEapClientMacs.description: This object specifies the global maximum number of non-EAP authenticated MAC addresses allowed.

bseeGuestVlanEnabled.name: bseeGuestVlanEnabled
bseeGuestVlanEnabled.description: This object specifies whether access to the global default guest VLAN is allowed.

bseeRemediationVlanEnabled.name: bseeRemediationVlanEnabled
bseeRemediationVlanEnabled.description: This object specifies whether access to the remediation VLAN is allowed.

bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapClient.name: bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapClient
bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapClient.description: This object controls whether non-EAP clients (MAC addresses) are allowed. This is the system-wide setting. The associated per-port setting (bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapClient) must also be true for non-EAP clients to be allowed on a particular port.

bseeMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapClient.name: bseeMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapClient
bseeMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapClient.description: This object controls whether non-EAP clients (MAC addresses) may be authenticated using RADIUS. This is the system-wide setting. The associated per-port setting (bseePortConfigMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapClient) must also be true for non-EAP clients to be authenticated using RADIUS on a particular port.

bseeMultiHostSingleAuthEnabled.name: bseeMultiHostSingleAuthEnabled
bseeMultiHostSingleAuthEnabled.description: This object controls whether non-EAP clients (MAC addresses) may be automatically authenticated on a port after an EAP client has been authenticated (known as MHSA). This is the system-wide setting. The associated per-port setting must also be true for non-EAP clients to be authenticated in this way.

bseeUserBasedPoliciesFilterOnMac.name: bseeUserBasedPoliciesFilterOnMac
bseeUserBasedPoliciesFilterOnMac.description: This object indicates whether the EAPOL User-based policy filters that are installed on ports will be dynamically modified to include the MAC address for which the filters are installed.

bseeMultiHostNonEapUserBasedPoliciesEnab.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapUserBasedPoliciesEnabled
bseeMultiHostNonEapUserBasedPoliciesEnab.description: This object indicates whether non-EAPOL User-based policies are enabled or disabled.

bseeMultiHostNonEapUserBasedPoliciesFilt.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapUserBasedPoliciesFilterOnMac
bseeMultiHostNonEapUserBasedPoliciesFilt.description: This object indicates whether the non-EAPOL User-based policy filters that are installed on ports will be dynamically modified to include the MAC address for which the filters are installed.

bseeMultihostNonEapRadiusPasswordAttribu.name: bseeMultihostNonEapRadiusPasswordAttributeFormat
bseeMultihostNonEapRadiusPasswordAttribu.description: This object controls the format of the RADIUS password attribute that is included in requests to the RADIUS server for authenticating non-EAP clients (MAC addresses). If the ipAddr(0) bit is set, the password attribute will contain the switch's IP address encoded as a string of four 3-digit 0-padded integers. For example, the encoding for the IP address 47.80.225.1 would be '047080225001'. If the macAddr(1) bit is set, the password attribute will contain the MAC address to be authenticated as a string of six 2-digit hex numbers. For example, the MAC address 00:08:01:0a:33:34 would be encoded as '0008010a3334'. If the portNumber(2) bit is set, the password attribute will contain the port number on which the MAC address was seen, encoded as a string of two 2-digit 0-padded integers. The first integer is the unit/slot number, and the second number is the port number on that unit/slot. For a standalone stackable unit, the unit/slot number will be 0. For example, the encoding for unit/port 1/23 would be '0123', and the encoding for port 7 on a standalone stackable unit would be '0007'. If the key(3) bit is set, the password attribute will contain a custom configured string of up to 32 characters in length. If padding(4) bit is set, the password will contain dots even if fields in the password are blank. For instance, IP and Key will be represented as IP...Key. If the bit is not set, there will be dots only to separate fields. IP and Key will be IP.Key, while IP, Mac, Port or Key alone will be as they are, with no dots. The fields in the password attribute will appear in the order of the bits defined in this object, i.e., IP addr, followed by MAC addr, followed by port number, and finally by the key. Fields are separated by a '.' character. The separators are present regardless of whether a field is present if padding is used. So, for example, if all four fields are present, the password attribute might contain: 047080225001.0008010a3334.0123.ERS4000isGreat If none of the three fields are present, the password attribute will be '...' with padding used, or '' with no padding.

bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapPhones.name: bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapPhones
bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapPhones.description: This object indicates whether IP phones will be allowed access based on DHCP.

bseeMultiHostAllowRadiusAssignedVlan.name: bseeMultiHostAllowRadiusAssignedVlan
bseeMultiHostAllowRadiusAssignedVlan.description: This object indicates whether to allow the use of RADIUS-assigned VLANs in multihost-eap mode.

bseeMultiHostEapPacketMode.name: bseeMultiHostEapPacketMode
bseeMultiHostEapPacketMode.description: This object indicates whether to use unicast or multicast packets for Eap-ReqId packets. Normally, multicast packets are used.

bseeMultiHostEapRadiusTimeoutMode.name: bseeMultiHostEapRadiusTimeoutMode
bseeMultiHostEapRadiusTimeoutMode.description: This object indicates whether or not to fail authentication of EAP users on a RADIUS timeout.

bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapRadiusAssignedVl.name: bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapRadiusAssignedVlan
bseeMultiHostAllowNonEapRadiusAssignedVl.description: This object indicates whether to allow the use of RADIUS-assigned VLANs in multihost-eap mode for non-EAP clients.

bseeMultiHostEapProtocolEnabled.name: bseeMultiHostEapProtocolEnabled
bseeMultiHostEapProtocolEnabled.description: This object controls whether processing of EAP protocol packets is enabled.

bseeMultiHostUseMostRecentRadiusAssigned.name: bseeMultiHostUseMostRecentRadiusAssignedVlan
bseeMultiHostUseMostRecentRadiusAssigned.description: Controls whether to use most recent RADIUS-assigned VLAN.

bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanId.name: bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanId
bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanId.description: This object specifies the ID of the global fail-over Vlan.

bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanEnabled.name: bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanEnabled
bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanEnabled.description: This object specifies whether to use the fail-over Vlan.

bseeMultiHostMultiVlan.name: bseeMultiHostMultiVlan
bseeMultiHostMultiVlan.description: This object specifies whether to use the multi-VLAN functionality with MHMA mode.

bseeMultiHostNeapReauthenticationEnabled.name: bseeMultiHostNeapReauthenticationEnabled
bseeMultiHostNeapReauthenticationEnabled.description: This object specifies whether to use 'NEAP re-authentication' feature

bseeMultiHostBlockDifferentVlanAuth.name: bseeMultiHostBlockDifferentVlanAuth
bseeMultiHostBlockDifferentVlanAuth.description: This object specifies whether to block authentication of clients which have an associated RADIUS assigned VLAN with an invalid value or different from first client authenticated on the same port

bseeMultiHostAdacDummyRadiusRequests.name: bseeMultiHostAdacDummyRadiusRequests
bseeMultiHostAdacDummyRadiusRequests.description: This object specifies whether to send or not dummy RADIUS requests for NEAP users authenticated as ADAC NEAP

bseeAllowPortMirroringOnEap.name: bseeAllowPortMirroringOnEap
bseeAllowPortMirroringOnEap.description: This object specifies whether EAP enabled ports can be involved in port mirroring

bseeMultiHostAdacNonEapEnabled.name: bseeMultiHostAdacNonEapEnabled
bseeMultiHostAdacNonEapEnabled.description: This object specifies whether the authentication of Non-EAP phones using ADAC is allowed.

bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanContinuityModeE.name: bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanContinuityModeEnabled
bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanContinuityModeE.description: This object specifies whether to use the fail-over Vlan continuity mode.

bseeMultiHostNonEapRadiusPasswordFreefor.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapRadiusPasswordFreeformKey
bseeMultiHostNonEapRadiusPasswordFreefor.description: This command specifies a custom string to be put in the password used to authenticate Non-EAP clients via RADIUS server.

bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanDisableEapMode.name: bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanDisableEapMode
bseeMultiHostFailOpenVlanDisableEapMode.description: This object specifies whether to use the Fail Open VLAN Disable EAP Mode.

bseePaeSystemOperState.name: bseePaeSystemOperState
bseePaeSystemOperState.description: The oper state of EAP when ports are in Fail Open VLAN Disable EAP Mode.

bseeDefaultEapAll.name: bseeDefaultEapAll
bseeDefaultEapAll.description: This object specifies whether to default all global EAP settings.

bseePortConfigTable.name: bseePortConfigTable
bseePortConfigTable.description: This table is used to control the EAP multihost configuration for each port in the system.

bseePortConfigEntry.name: bseePortConfigEntry
bseePortConfigEntry.description: The EAP multihost configuration for a port.

bseePortConfigPortNumber.name: bseePortConfigPortNumber
bseePortConfigPortNumber.description: The Port number associated with this Port.

bseePortConfigGuestVlanId.name: bseePortConfigGuestVlanId
bseePortConfigGuestVlanId.description: This object specifies the ID of the guest VLAN for this port. Access to the guest VLAN is allowed for MAC addresses before EAP authentication has been performed. If the value of this object is 0, then the global guest VLAN ID is used for this port, as specified in bseeGuestVlanId. However, if the value of the associated instance of bseePortConfigGuestVlanEnabled is false(2), then access to the guest VLAN is not allowed for the port, regardless of the value of bseePortConfigGuestVlanId.

bseePortConfigMultiHostEnabled.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostEnabled
bseePortConfigMultiHostEnabled.description: This object controls whether EAP multihost is enabled for a port.

bseePortConfigMultiHostEapMaxNumMacs.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostEapMaxNumMacs
bseePortConfigMultiHostEapMaxNumMacs.description: This object specifies the maximum number of EAP-authentication MAC addresses allowed on this port. A value of 0 indicates that there is no port-specific limit.

bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapClient.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapClient
bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapClient.description: This object controls whether non-EAP clients (MAC addresses) are allowed on the port.

bseePortConfigMultiHostNonEapMacSource.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostNonEapMacSource
bseePortConfigMultiHostNonEapMacSource.description: This object controls the source for finding allowed non-EAP MAC addresses.

bseePortConfigMultiHostNonEapMaxNumMacs.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostNonEapMaxNumMacs
bseePortConfigMultiHostNonEapMaxNumMacs.description: This object specifies the maximum number of non-EAP authenticated MAC addresses allowed on this port.

bseePortConfigGuestVlanEnabled.name: bseePortConfigGuestVlanEnabled
bseePortConfigGuestVlanEnabled.description: This object controls whether access to the guest VLAN is allowed for a port.

bseePortConfigMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapC.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapClient
bseePortConfigMultiHostRadiusAuthNonEapC.description: This object controls whether non-EAP clients (MAC addresses) may authenticated using RADIUS on the port.

bseePortConfigMultiHostSingleAuthEnabled.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostSingleAuthEnabled
bseePortConfigMultiHostSingleAuthEnabled.description: This object controls whether non-EAP clients (MAC addresses) may be automatically authenticated on the port after an EAP client has been authenticated (known as MHSA).

bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapPhones.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapPhones
bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapPhones.description: This object indicates whether IP phones will be allowed access based on DHCP.

bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowRadiusAssign.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowRadiusAssignedVlan
bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowRadiusAssign.description: This object indicates whether to allow the use of RADIUS-assigned VLANs in multihost-eap mode.

bseePortConfigMultiHostEapPacketMode.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostEapPacketMode
bseePortConfigMultiHostEapPacketMode.description: This object indicates whether to use unicast or multicast packets for Eap-ReqId packets. Normally, multicast packets are used.

bseePortConfigMultiHostEapRadiusTimeoutM.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostEapRadiusTimeoutMode
bseePortConfigMultiHostEapRadiusTimeoutM.description: This object indicates whether or not to fail authentication of EAP users on a RADIUS timeout.

bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapRadius.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapRadiusAssignedVlan
bseePortConfigMultiHostAllowNonEapRadius.description: This object indicates whether to allow the use of RADIUS-assigned VLANs in multihost-eap mode for non-EAP clients.

bseePortConfigProcessRadiusRequestsServe.name: bseePortConfigProcessRadiusRequestsServerPackets
bseePortConfigProcessRadiusRequestsServe.description: This object indicates whether to process any RADIUS requests-server packets that are received on this port.

bseePortConfigEapProtocolEnabled.name: bseePortConfigEapProtocolEnabled
bseePortConfigEapProtocolEnabled.description: This object controls whether EAP protocol packets are processed on this port.

bseePortConfigMultiHostUseMostRecentRadi.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostUseMostRecentRadiusAssignedVlan
bseePortConfigMultiHostUseMostRecentRadi.description: Controls whether to use most recent RADIUS-assigned VLAN.

bseePortConfigMultiHostClearNeap.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostClearNeap
bseePortConfigMultiHostClearNeap.description: Setting this object will clear NEAP authenticated clients from the authentication list. If the value is set to 00:00:00:00:00:00, all clients will be cleared from this port. Otherwise, only a specific client will be cleared.

bseePortConfigMultiHostBlockDifferentVla.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostBlockDifferentVlanAuth
bseePortConfigMultiHostBlockDifferentVla.description: Controls whether to block authentication of clients which have an associated RADIUS assigned VLAN with an invalid value or different from first client authenticated on the same port.

bseePortConfigMultiHostAdacNonEapEnabled.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostAdacNonEapEnabled
bseePortConfigMultiHostAdacNonEapEnabled.description: This object specifies whether the authentication of Non-EAP phones using ADAC is allowed on this port.

bseePortConfigDefaultEapAll.name: bseePortConfigDefaultEapAll
bseePortConfigDefaultEapAll.description: This object specifies whether to default all EAP settings on this port.

bseePortConfigMultiHostMaxMacs.name: bseePortConfigMultiHostMaxMacs
bseePortConfigMultiHostMaxMacs.description: This object specifies the maximum number of EAP and NEAP clients allowed on this port.

bseeMultiHostStatusTable.name: bseeMultiHostStatusTable
bseeMultiHostStatusTable.description: This table provides the EAP authentication status per-MAC address per-port.

bseeMultiHostStatusEntry.name: bseeMultiHostStatusEntry
bseeMultiHostStatusEntry.description: The status of EAP authentication of clients for a port.

bseeMultiHostStatusPortNumber.name: bseeMultiHostStatusPortNumber
bseeMultiHostStatusPortNumber.description: The Port number associated with this client.

bseeMultiHostStatusClientMACAddr.name: bseeMultiHostStatusClientMACAddr
bseeMultiHostStatusClientMACAddr.description: The MAC address of the client.

bseeMultiHostStatusPaeState.name: bseeMultiHostStatusPaeState
bseeMultiHostStatusPaeState.description: The current value of the Authenticator PAE state machine.

bseeMultiHostStatusBackendAuthState.name: bseeMultiHostStatusBackendAuthState
bseeMultiHostStatusBackendAuthState.description: The current state of the Backend Authentication state machine.

bseeMultiHostStatusReauthenticate.name: bseeMultiHostStatusReauthenticate
bseeMultiHostStatusReauthenticate.description: Setting this object to reauthenticate(2) will force the client to be reauthenticated. When retrieved, the value of this object is always other(1).

bseeMultiHostStatusVid.name: bseeMultiHostStatusVid
bseeMultiHostStatusVid.description: The Vlan ID associated with this client for MultiVlan capabilities. If MultiVlan is not enabled for this client, the value of this object will be 4095.

bseeMultiHostStatusPri.name: bseeMultiHostStatusPri
bseeMultiHostStatusPri.description: The Vlan priority value associated with this client for MultiVlan capabilities. If MultiVlan is not enabled for this client, the value of this object will be 8.

bseeMultiHostSessionStatsTable.name: bseeMultiHostSessionStatsTable
bseeMultiHostSessionStatsTable.description: A table that contains the session statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each EAP client on each Port. An entry appears in this table for each client MAC address on each port that may authenticate access to itself.

bseeMultiHostSessionStatsEntry.name: bseeMultiHostSessionStatsEntry
bseeMultiHostSessionStatsEntry.description: The session statistics information for an Authenticator PAE. This shows the current values being collected for each session that is still in progress, or the final values for the last valid session for each client where there is no session currently active. This is similar to the dot1xAuthSessionStatsTable, except that it provides information per-port-per-MAC, rather than just per-port.

bseeMultiHostSessionStatsPortNumber.name: bseeMultiHostSessionStatsPortNumber
bseeMultiHostSessionStatsPortNumber.description: The Port number associated with this client.

bseeMultiHostSessionStatsClientMACAddr.name: bseeMultiHostSessionStatsClientMACAddr
bseeMultiHostSessionStatsClientMACAddr.description: The MAC address of this client.

bseeMultiHostSessionId.name: bseeMultiHostSessionId
bseeMultiHostSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

bseeMultiHostSessionAuthenticMethod.name: bseeMultiHostSessionAuthenticMethod
bseeMultiHostSessionAuthenticMethod.description: The authentication method used to establish the session.

bseeMultiHostSessionTime.name: bseeMultiHostSessionTime
bseeMultiHostSessionTime.description: The duration of the session in seconds.

bseeMultiHostSessionTerminateCause.name: bseeMultiHostSessionTerminateCause
bseeMultiHostSessionTerminateCause.description: The reason for the session termination.

bseeMultiHostSessionUserName.name: bseeMultiHostSessionUserName
bseeMultiHostSessionUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

bseeMultiHostNonEapMacTable.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapMacTable
bseeMultiHostNonEapMacTable.description: A table that contains the non-EAP MAC addresses that are allowed access to EAP-enabled interfaces.

bseeMultiHostNonEapMacPortNumber.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapMacPortNumber
bseeMultiHostNonEapMacPortNumber.description: The Port number on which the MAC address is allowed.

bseeMultiHostNonEapMacClientMACAddr.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapMacClientMACAddr
bseeMultiHostNonEapMacClientMACAddr.description: The MAC address allowed on the port.

bseeMultiHostNonEapMacRowStatus.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapMacRowStatus
bseeMultiHostNonEapMacRowStatus.description: This is used to control creation/deletion of entries in this table.

bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusTable.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusTable
bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusTable.description: This table provides the authentication status of non-EAP clients per-MAC address per-port.

bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusEntry.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusEntry
bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusEntry.description: The status of authentication of a non-EAP client for a port.

bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusPortNumber.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusPortNumber
bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusPortNumber.description: The Port number associated with this client.

bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusClientMACAddr.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusClientMACAddr
bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusClientMACAddr.description: The MAC address of the client.

bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusState.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusState
bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusState.description: The authentication status. Values are: rejected(1) - the MAC address could not be authenticated on this port locallyAuthenticated(2) - the MAC address was authenticated using the local table of allowed clients radiusPending(3) - the MAC address is awaiting authentication by a RADIUS server radiusAuthenticated(4) - the MAC address was authenticated by a RADIUS server adacAuthenticated(5) - the MAC address was authenticated using ADAC configuration tables mhsaAuthenticated(6) - the MAC address was auto-authenticated on a port following a successful authentication of an EAP client

bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusReauthenticate.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusReauthenticate
bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusReauthenticate.description: Setting this object to reauthenticate(2) will force the MAC address to be reauthenticated. When retrieved, the value of this object is always other(1).

bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusVid.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusVid
bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusVid.description: The Vlan ID associated with this client for MultiVlan capabilities. If MultiVlan is not enabled for this client, the value of this object will be 4095.

bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusPri.name: bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusPri
bseeMultiHostNonEapStatusPri.description: The Vlan priority value associated with this client for MultiVlan capabilities. If MultiVlan is not enabled for this client, the value of this object will be 8.

bseeSupplicantEnabled.name: bseeSupplicantEnabled
bseeSupplicantEnabled.description: Indicates whether supplicant functionality is enabled or disabled. A value of true(1) means enabled.

bseeSupplicantUserTable.name: bseeSupplicantUserTable
bseeSupplicantUserTable.description: A table that contains the user name and password for the Supplicant PAE associated with each port. An entry appears in this table for each port that may authenticate itself when challenged by a remote system.

bseeSupplicantUserEntry.name: bseeSupplicantUserEntry
bseeSupplicantUserEntry.description: The configuration information for a Supplicant PAE.

bseeSupplicantPortNumber.name: bseeSupplicantPortNumber
bseeSupplicantPortNumber.description: A unique value for each interface. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of ifNumber. The value for each interface must remain constant at least from one re-initialization of the entity's network management system to the next re- initialization.

bseeSupplicantUserName.name: bseeSupplicantUserName
bseeSupplicantUserName.description: The user name currently in use by the Supplicant PAE state machine.

bseeSupplicantPassword.name: bseeSupplicantPassword
bseeSupplicantPassword.description: The password currently in use by the Supplicant PAE state machine.

bseeSupplicantUserState.name: bseeSupplicantUserState
bseeSupplicantUserState.description: Input the user state to logoff.

bseeMultiHostVoipVlanTable.name: bseeMultiHostVoipVlanTable
bseeMultiHostVoipVlanTable.description: A table that contains EAP VoIP Vlan settings.

bseeMultiHostVoipVlanEntry.name: bseeMultiHostVoipVlanEntry
bseeMultiHostVoipVlanEntry.description: The configuration information for an EAP VoIP Vlan.

bseeMultiHostVoipVlanIndex.name: bseeMultiHostVoipVlanIndex
bseeMultiHostVoipVlanIndex.description: A unique identifier for each entry.

bseeMultiHostVoipVlanId.name: bseeMultiHostVoipVlanId
bseeMultiHostVoipVlanId.description: This object specifies the Vlan ID of the VoIP Vlan.

bseeMultiHostVoipVlanEnabled.name: bseeMultiHostVoipVlanEnabled
bseeMultiHostVoipVlanEnabled.description: This object specifies whether to use this VoIP Vlan.

bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneTable.name: bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneTable
bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneTable.description: This table provides the list of DHCP authenticated IP phones per-MAC address per-port.

bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneEntry.name: bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneEntry
bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneEntry.description: The DHCP authenticated IP phone for a port.

bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhonePortNumber.name: bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhonePortNumber
bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhonePortNumber.description: The port number associated with the DHCP authenticated IP phone.

bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneClientMACAddr.name: bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneClientMACAddr
bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneClientMACAddr.description: The MAC address of the DHCP authenticated IP phone.

bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneUserName.name: bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneUserName
bseeMultiHostDhcpAuthPhoneUserName.description: The user name currently in use by the DHCP authenticated IP phone.
